width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jebbar>Jebbar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 296<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/2/03 12:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4984.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warrior ideas</span><hr size=1> First off, I'd like to say I'm in the &quot;FIX TAUNT&quot; camp. Warriors rock in the right situations, but until warrior taunt (and ONLY warrior taunt) is changed, they will be broken. Once a class is only wanted for one single ability (the ability in this case being /disc defensive), that class is broken.<br>
<br>
Now, on to some silly statements I read, and my rebuttals.<br>
<br>
Vicaire said:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Why take a warrior anymore when knights tank the same and you get a rezzer/buffer/healer/situationally outstanding dps class or a strong dps class that can FD pull, give the group FT 10/regen 10/atk 100 and procs lifetaps so much on slowed mobs they don't even need healing a lot of the time.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Knights have CRAPPY DPS. Knights are FAR, FAR from &quot;outstanding DPS classes.&quot; Yes, paladins can do respectable DPS when fighting undead, but if we're going to make that distinction, then CLERICS are an &quot;outstanding DPS&quot; class. Paladins and Shadowknights are not wanted for their DPS (which is down near the worst in the game, btw) but for ability to near-instantly grab and hold agro, something warriors just can't do.<br>
<br>
Hurren said:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Warriors should generate the most damage of any class.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
/boggle. Um. Warriors aren't a DPS class. Warriors soak damage, they do not deal it. You're saying warriors should deal more damage than wizards? Rogues? Mages? I couldn't disagree more. One of the problems with class balance right now is that a warrior with smart AA and decent weapons can outdamage a similarly equipped monk, provided the warrior isn't tanking. That, in my opinion, ain't right.<br>
<br>
Hurren also said:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The rest of the melee classes (well except for monks, but they get their special attacks, though Ive never played one, so I have no idea on how much damge they really do) get an assortment of spells.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
There are three melee classes. Rogue, monk and warrior. None of them get any spells. That's what a pure melee is--a character without any spells.<br>
<br>
Hurren ALSO said:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>All I need is to do the maximum damage, and right now<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Play a rogue, ranger or wizard then. Your job is not to deal damage. If you really like dealing damage (which it seems you do), warrior is the wrong class for you.<br>
<br>
Sylexis said (in response to the statement that warriors can't effectively solo):<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>They already can.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Sure, with 100k+ in gear they can. So what she really means is if you're a twink or an ebayer you can solo. Please, Sylexis, enlighten us on exactly what gear they'd need to buy, and where they'd need to go to solo. I'm sorry, in my eyes a class who needs to spend 100k+ and go to only very specific zones to solo, can't *effectively* solo.<br>
<br>
Sajuiil said (paraphrasing one of the melee boards):<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>rogues are useless compared to wizards<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I'd like to see what melee board implies this. Rogues, out of all the pure melees, are the least broken imo. They do what they are supposed to do--deal HUGE amounts of damage and shed agro if necessary.<br>
<br>
Keep up the good fight, warriors. I'm rooting for you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
