<br>
And as far as rogues go there is a fun bit circulating in the rogue community: with the new LDoN expansion the assassination mission can be completed by any single class group of 6 except rogues /boggle (of course its not true but as I said every class thinks they got it the worst). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vicairedelestacia>Vicaire Delestacia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/2/03 4:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4984.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warrior ideas</span><hr size=1> Warrior dps is quite a bit lower than shadowknight dps assuming equal gear.  Paladin dps can situationally, i.e lots of undead, blow both away.  Generally the dps curve looks like SKs &gt; warriors &gt; paladins.<br>
<br>
 A SK that tries can sustain a respectable amount of sustained dps in an equally leveled and geared group in the 60 plus range. SK dps is nothing to brag about but warriors fare badly in comparison which is an important factor in this discussion.<br>
<br>
Paladins in an undead enviroment with SU3 and BoN are an incredibly outstanding dps class.  I have seen them put rogues to shame easily. Paladins can at times beat mages, arguably the best sustained general dps class around,  for sustained dps in an undead enviroment.  <br>
